  "decision_conditions": [
    "<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin: 0pt 2pt 0pt -7pt; padding: 0pt 5.4pt;\">&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin: 0pt 2pt 0pt -7pt; padding: 0pt 5.4pt;\"><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\">The proposed roof terrace at upper ground floor level, by reason of its size, design and position, would result in loss of privacy and overlooking to neighbouring windows and their amenity space that would result in an unacceptable adverse impact on the amenity of the neighbouring occupiers, particularly 91 Albion Road. As such the proposed development is contrary to policy D1 (London’s form, character and capacity for growth) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP2 (Development and amenity) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020) and the guidance contained within Hackney Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document (2009).</span></p><p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-c46411c2-7fff-91cb-ae7b-05392f0011d5\"></span></p>",
    "<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin: 0pt 2pt 0pt -7pt; padding: 0pt 5.4pt;\">&nbsp;The proposed roof terrace by reason of its design, scale and position would result in the introduction of an incongruous addition that fails to respect the character and appearance of the subject building or wider terrace, contrary to&nbsp; policies D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach) and D4 (Delivering good design) of the London Plan (2021) and Policy LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character)&nbsp; of the Hackney Local Plan (2020) the relevant sections of the Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document (2009).</p><p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ac26a15e-7fff-84bb-40e1-c6ecfa113479\"></span></p>"
  ],
